Pre-Game Insights: The Namibia Cricket Team will take on the Netherlands in Match 5 of the ICC T20 World Cup 2022 Qualifiers on Tuesday, October 18 at the Simonds Stadium in Geelong.
Both teams are heading into the match on the back of brilliant wins in their first match at the same venue.
Namibia pulled off a great performance to defeat Sri Lanka on Sunday by 55 runs.
The Netherlands also secured a good win against the United Arab Emirates by three wickets.
Both Namibia and Netherlands will be keen to continue their winning run and consolidate their position in the Qualifiers points table.
An equal contest between bat and ball can be expected at the Simonds Stadium in Geelong. The team that wins the toss will look to bowl first. 160 should be a good total at the venue.
